HELP.Diagnostic_Loading_time_LOADING_TIME:
This part shows how quickly users are able to see and interact with content.

You can use the Loading Time report to measure where load times for your pages are having a critical impact.

Avg Page Load Time : The average amount of time (in seconds) it takes that page to load, from initiation of the pageview (e.g., click on a page link) to load completion in the browser.

This metric is composed of six elements: 1) "Avg. Redirection Time", 2) "Avg. Domain Lookup", 3) "Avg. Server Connection Time", 4) "Avg. Server Response Time", 5) "Avg. Page Download Time", and 6) "Avg. Browser Time".

HELP.SEA_Keywords_Negative_keywords_SEARCH_TE: Shows the percentage of suspicious search terms among all the search terms of the account from the last month.
HELP.SEA_Keywords_Negative_keywords_NEGATIVE_: Shows the number of remaining and already treated suspicious search terms, and the evolution  since the last period (from the above line chart). Shows also an expected gain on the global CTR after the treatment of all the suspicious search terms.
HELP.SEA_Keywords_Negative_keywords_Create_ne: This part allows you to create a negative keywords list that will be kept in Monetoring. You can apply this list on the campaigns and ad-groups you want through the right part of this box.
HELP.SEA_Keywords_Negative_keywords_Edit_new_: This part allows you to edit a negative keywords list that will be kept in Monetoring. You can apply this list on the campaigns and ad-groups you want through the right part of this box.
HELP.SEA_Keywords_Negative_keywords_RECOMMEND:
On this table you can find the recommendation for negative keywords, and their origin.
The Search terms column contain the suspicious search terms, and the Proposed negative keywords column contain the associated negative keyword for this search term. You can directly modify the negative keyword by clicking on it, and then pressing the enter after your modification.
The Action column allows you to directly add the negative keyword to the ad-group (green button), to add the negative keyword to an existing list (blue button), or to remove it from the table (red button), in case you find that the recommendation is not relevant.
HELP.SEA_Keywords_Negative_keywords_CHANGE_HI: In this table you can find all the modifications done through this interface, with all the details (when, who, action done, …) and you can also cancel a modification.
HELP.SEA_Ads: The Action column allows you to directly add the negative keyword to the ad-group (green button), to add the negative keyword to an existing list (blue button), or to remove it from the table (red button), in case you find that the recommendation is not relevant.
HELP.SEA_Ads_View: Here you can compare the performances of your ads, and find more details by clicking on each ads. The Match column gives you the match score between ads and landing pages, and between ads and keywords.
HELP.SEA_Ads_KEYWORDS: Here are the keywords of the ad-group for which your ad appears.
HELP.SEA_Ads_SEMANTIC_RECOMMENDATIONS: Here you can find the semantic recommendations that we calculate from your competitors ads.
HELP.SEA_Ads_TOP_SEARCH_TERMS: This chart shows the most common search terms for this ad considering the keywords that activate it. the bigger the circle, the bigger the frequency.
HELP.SEA_Ads_TOP_RECURRENT_WORDS: This chart shows the most recurrent words within your search terms, minus the keywords you are already bidding on.
HELP.SEA_Ads_Create_new_ad_AD_CREATION_TOOL: After selecting a campaign and an ad-group, you can create new ads or modify existing ads from the selected ad-group. The Semantic Recommendation part is here to help you, by giving you the most important words from your competitors ads. You can also click on the ads from Existing Ads part to automatically fill the form before modifying it.
HELP.SEA_Benchmark_Competitors: This diagram shows the evolution of some metrics from you and your competitor's performances. By selecting a date range you can see the evolution over time.
HELP.SEA_Benchmark_Competitors_COMPETITORS_CH:
In those two charts you can find all your competitors from the last month and their performances comparing to yours.
In the left chart, three red circles shows your website values, that you can compare to your competitors.
In the right chart, the size of circles represent the impression share of each competitor. Competitors in the red zone are considered “critical” : they are higher than you at least 56% of the time, on all your impressions. The orange zone means that they are higher at least 25% of the time.
-Top of page rate : percentage of impression above the SEO results;
-Outranking share : percentage of impression where your ad is higher than the competitor’s ad, or when your competitor’s ad doesn’t appears.
-Overlap rate : percentage of impression where your ad and the competitor’s ad are shown for the same auction on the SERP.
-Position above rate : percentage of impression where your competitor's ad is shown at a higher position than yours, when both of them are shownat the same time.
